On 1/12/05 8:11 PM, "David Schwarze" <schwarze(-at-)mail.ev1.net> wrote:

> I agree that they are good as deep discharging batteries but I must point
> out that two important characteristics of AGM (absorbed glass mat)
> batteries such as the Optima are:
> 
> 1.  Long shelf life (low internal discharge rate)
> 2.  Very high discharge rate capability

I was skeptical of them mostly because the Porsche crowd raved about them
;-) but tried a Yuasa AGM battery out when my motorcycle battery failed. I
no longer have to disconnect the battery when the bike is not in frequent
use to prevent it from draining down.

